I work at the International Spy Museum across the street from this location. I go here for lunch often along with many other staff at the museum. Today, one of my employees went across the street for her lunch break and her phone was misplaced. She realized when she got back to the museum that she didn't have her phone. She went back to speak to management only to find an empty restaurant and the staff huddled strangely in the back. She said she left her phone and the staff said NO. She looked around and left upset. We called it and the phone had been turned off indicating that someone has intercepted it. One of our managers went across the street to ask about the phone and was given the same answer with an attitude. He asked to see the camera footage that is prominently displayed above the register. The cashier and owner, Shamsul Mollah, said he doesn't know how to operate the cameras. We asked what they would do if they were robbed and he said, "I don't know." At this point we could only assume that a Subway team member had stolen the phone. Based on their behavior in the huddle, lack of cooperation with the cameras and overall rudeness, I can safely recommend no one eating at this location. Subway HQ, please help!
